It must answer:

How does doctor labeling change the model over time?

Let’s design this properly.

🎯 Core Story Your Dashboard Must Tell

Your dashboard should visually communicate six evolving dynamics:

What sample is being queried?

Why is it queried? (uncertainty)

How is the model evolving?

Which features are driving decisions?

How class errors change?

How performance improves with fewer labels?

🧠 Dashboard Architecture (Proposal-Ready)

I recommend a 3-layer layout:

---------------------------------------------------
TOP: Model Understanding
MIDDLE: Doctor Interaction
BOTTOM: Performance Evolution
---------------------------------------------------

Let’s define each.

🔵 TOP PANEL – MODEL UNDERSTANDING
1️⃣ Feature Importance Evolution

Visualization: Horizontal bar chart
Data: Logistic regression coefficients
Update: After each retraining

Show:
• Signed coefficients
• Absolute magnitude
• Evolution over rounds

Why critical?
Because:

Your features are engineered.

Doctors must see which EEG properties matter.

It connects ML to domain science.

Advanced idea:
Add small timeline slider to show coefficient drift.

2️⃣ Embedding View (2D Projection)

Use PCA or UMAP on your 10 features.

Visualization: Scatter plot

Color:
• Labeled samples
• Unlabeled samples
• Queried samples (highlighted)
• True seizure vs non-seizure (optional toggle)

Why critical?

It shows:

Where uncertainty clusters

Whether seizure samples form a cluster

How labeled region expands

Add interaction:
• Hover shows feature values
• Click shows EEG in inspection panel

This is powerful.

🟡 MIDDLE PANEL – DOCTOR INTERACTION

This is your core.

3️⃣ Uncertain EEG Viewer

Display:

• Raw EEG waveform
• Model predicted probability
• Uncertainty score

Add:

Probability of Seizure: 0.52
Uncertainty: 0.48

Why important?

Doctors must see why it's queried.

4️⃣ Uncertainty Distribution Histogram

Plot:

Histogram of model confidence over unlabeled pool.

Highlight:
• Selected sample

This visually proves:

“We are selecting boundary cases.”

Without this, active learning claim is weak.

🟢 BOTTOM PANEL – PERFORMANCE EVOLUTION
5️⃣ Learning Curve (Primary Evidence)

X-axis: Labeled samples
Y-axis: Test accuracy

Add:
• Vertical lines at batch retraining points
• Show random baseline (optional)

Add dropdown:
• Accuracy
• Sensitivity
• Specificity
• F1

Because in medicine accuracy alone is insufficient.

6️⃣ Confusion Matrix + Metric Trends

Two parts:

A) Confusion Matrix Heatmap

Update after each retraining.

B) Metric Trend Line Plot

Plot over rounds:
• Sensitivity
• Specificity
• F1-score

This shows:

“Doctor labeling improves seizure detection specifically.”

That’s clinically powerful.

🧠 Advanced but Strong Additions

If you want to impress reviewers:

7️⃣ Error Inspection Panel

Allow doctor to click:

• False positives
• False negatives

And inspect those EEGs.

Shows transparency.

8️⃣ Labeling Efficiency Plot

Plot:

Accuracy vs % labeled data

Add comparison:

Random sampling vs uncertainty sampling.

Even simulated once.

This proves active learning advantage.

